---
import { Collapse, Icon, Spoiler, Timeline } from 'astro-pure/user'
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/CommonPage.astro'

const headings = [
  { depth: 2, slug: 'social-networks', text: 'Social Networks' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'experience', text: 'Experience' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'academic-activities', text: 'Academic Activities' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'side-projects', text: 'Side Projects' }
]
---

<PageLayout title='About' {headings}>
  <p>
    I am currently a Research Scientist at <a href='https://seed.bytedance.com/en/' target='_blank' >ByteDance Seed</a>, 
    specializing in the AI for Science team under the leadership of <a href='https://web.cs.ucla.edu/~qgu/' target='_blank'>
    Prof. Quanquan Gu</a>. My previous research includes topics about <u>generative models</u>, <u>computer vision</u>, and
    <u>cryo-electron microscopy (cryo-EM)</u>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Prior to my current role, I worked with
    <a href='https://www.bytedance.com/en/' target='_blank'>ByteDance</a>'s Education Team, focusing
    on business algorithms. Before that, I served as a Computer Vision Researcher in
    <a href='https://www.sensetime.com/en' target='_blank'>SenseTime</a>'s Medical Team. I earned my
    Master's degree from
    <a href='https://en.ustc.edu.cn/' target='_blank'>University of Science and Technology of China</a>
    in 2019, where I concentrated on image saliency detection.
  </p>
  <p>
    <Spoiler>Always Day One.</Spoiler>
  </p>

